elements.title: National Windrush Monument
elements.contents: ... that the National Windrush Monument (pictured) features a family standing on a pile of suitcases and "surveying their new country"?

elements.title: a drawing of a dog
elements.contents: ... that a drawing of a dog was promoted by the president of El Salvador, caused an unaffiliated song to peak on the TikTok Billboard Top 50, and got its original creator doxxed?

elements.title: Mandenga Diek
elements.contents: ... that the naturalised German Mandenga Diek was denied funds to return to his native Cameroon because he wanted to bring his German wife?

elements.title: the city's actual tornadoes
elements.contents: ... that Chicago's tornado siren has been described as creepier than the city's actual tornadoes?

elements.title: Mickey Volcan
elements.contents: ... that a snowstorm resulted in Mickey Volcan and Garry Howatt becoming the first active players to officiate a National Hockey League game?

elements.title: Església de Sant Serni de Canillo
elements.contents: ... that Església de Sant Serni de Canillo has the tallest bell tower in Andorra?

elements.title: The First Girl I Loved
elements.contents: ... that the director of the lesbian film The First Girl I Loved based the plot on true stories gathered from all-girls school graduates he interviewed?

elements.title: Leo Franciosi
elements.contents: ... that butcher Leo Franciosi was also a four-time Olympian?

elements.title: Pseudo-Evodius
